<s> The problem here is not with install-sh itself, but rather, it's due to the fact that `../install-sh' is an incorrect path to this script at the time it's being invoked.  </s>
<s> Therefore, if `install-sh' was replaced with `shtool' and if nothing else was changed in the build process, an identical error would occur if the build were trying to invoke `../shtool install'.  </s>
<s> In the above case, was the configure script run as `../configure' from within the `Sun-Sparc-Solaris-2.5.1' directory?  </s>
